    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><persName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Littera/mandatum #Fiscal_property #Function #Redistributive #Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/124">Federicus</persName> Dei gratia
                        Romanorum <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> et semper agustus.
                        Imperatorie maiestatis deposcit officium, quatinus in manutenenda et
                        conservanda iusticia principaliter studium et diligentiam inpendamus, ut,
                        que iniuste possideri decernuntur et maxime ab inimicis imperii bone fidei
                        possessori nostri auctoritate reddantur. Ideoque <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >ecclesie</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/47"
                            key="#Monasteries #Abbots">sancti Silvestri</orgName> de <placeName
                            ref="#places/15" key="#Monasteries"
                            >Nonantula</placeName> possessionem, quam <persName key="#Local_elites"
                            ref="#people/128">Turisendus</persName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/59">Veronensis</placeName> in
                            <rs
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive"
                            >loco</rs>
                        <placeName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive"
                            ref="#places/145">Nogarie</placeName> vel eius
                            <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive"
                            ref="#estates/116">curia</geogName> iniuste tenet
                        vel possidet, reddimus atque restituimus eo pacto, quod quocumque tempore
                        nos vel <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/129">filius noster
                        </persName>illustris rex Romanorum vel alius noster successor Nonantulane
                        ecclesie <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">censum vel pensionem,</rs>
                        quam <rs key="#Countess">comitissa</rs>
                        <persName key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Function #Redistributive #Countess"
                            ref="#people/125">Matildis</persName> vel
                        antecesores nostri imperator <persName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Function #Redistributive #Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/127">Enricus</persName> et rex
                            <persName key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Function #Redistributive"
                            ref="#people/126">Conradus</persName> inde
                        solvere consueverunt, predicte ecclesie solvere voluerint, <rs key="#Abbots"
                            >abas</rs> Nonantolanus et eius succesores vel ecclesia Nonantulana
                        illum censum recipiat et nos nostrosque subcesores sub iam dicto canone
                        predictam possesionem sine contradictione tenere permittat. Unde statuentes
                        precipimus atque sancimus, ut nullus temeraria presumcione prefactam
                        ecclesiam in predicta possesione inpediat vel inquietare presumat. Si quis
                        autem contra hoc nostrum decretum facere presumserit, eterni iudicis
                        disstrictam subibit sentenciam et pro consuetudine nostre curie multabitur
                        et temporali pena punietur. Et ut hoc firmius credatur et in posterum
                        perseveret, presentem <rs key="#Littera/mandatum">paginam</rs> sigillo
                        nostro munivimus atque firmavimus. <date>Data Altoburgii anno milesimo
                            centesimo octoagesimo, indictione quartadecima, nono decimo die mensis
                            octubris.</date></ab>
                </div>
